  "issue_title": "[bug] memory/inject: per-turn hydration can exceed 700-token M1 budget with no runtime cap",
  "issue_body": "### Summary\n\n`agent_harness::MEMORY_HYDRATION_BUDGET_TOKENS` (700) is documented in M1 and checked by `validate_limited_context_agent()`, but `memory::inject::build_memory_context()` never enforces that budget at runtime. It can assemble up to ~13 memory lines with no token estimate or truncation, so live chat/voice turns can blow the Jetson context contract even when boot-time harness checks pass on a smaller sample.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. On an x86_64 Linux dev host:\n   ```bash\n   cd genie-claw\n   ```\n2. Confirm the harness budget exists but inject does not use it:\n   ```bash\n   grep -n MEMORY_HYDRATION_BUDGET_TOKENS crates/genie-core/src/agent_harness.rs\n   grep -n MEMORY_HYDRATION_BUDGET_TOKENS crates/genie-core/src/memory/inject.rs\n   ```\n   **Pass (bug present):** budget constant appears in `agent_harness.rs` only; `inject.rs` has no matches.\n3. Confirm inject caps entry *count* loosely but not tokens, and search can push past the `8` entry soft limit used for preferences:\n   ```bash\n   sed -n '42,83p' crates/genie-core/src/memory/inject.rs\n   ```\n   **Pass:** identity (5) + relationship (3) + search (5) can yield up to 13 lines; only the preference block checks `entries.len() < 8`.\n4. Add a unit test in `memory/inject.rs` (or run in `cargo test` after adding):\n   ```rust\n   #[test]\n   fn hydration_exceeds_700_token_budget_without_cap() {\n       let mem = temp_memory();\n       let long = \"household detail sentence. \".repeat(20); // ~520 chars each\n       for i in 0..13 {\n           mem.store(\"identity\", &format!(\"{long} #{i}\")).unwrap();\n       }\n       let ctx = build_memory_context(&mem, \"turn on the kitchen lights\");\n       let tokens = crate::agent_harness::estimate_tokens(&ctx);\n       assert!(tokens <= crate::agent_harness::MEMORY_HYDRATION_BUDGET_TOKENS);\n       // FAILS on main \u2014 tokens >> 700\n   }\n   ```\n5. Compare with harness test that only checks the API in isolation:\n   ```bash\n   cargo test -p genie-core oversized_memory_hydration_fails_the_harness\n   ```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n- Per-turn `build_memory_context()` output stays within `MEMORY_HYDRATION_BUDGET_TOKENS` (700) using the same `estimate_tokens()` heuristic as the harness, or documents an explicit truncation/priority policy (identity > relationship > query-relevant > preference).\n- Oversized hydration emits structured `tracing::warn` with estimated tokens and dropped entry count.\n- M1 chat/voice turns do not silently consume prompt budget beyond the documented Jetson contract.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\n- `build_memory_context()` joins all selected entries with no token accounting.\n- Up to ~13 entries can be injected; long promoted/profile memories can exceed 700 tokens in one turn.\n- Harness may pass at boot (empty or small DB, single sample query) while production memory growth breaks the budget on every subsequent turn.\n\n### Hardware\n\nNon-Jetson (x86_64 dev / cross-build host)\n\n### JetPack / L4T version\n\n_No response_\n\n### GenieClaw version / commit\n\nv1.0.0-alpha.10 / `main`\n\n### Relevant logs\n\n```shell\n\n```\n\n### Additional context\n\n**Suggested files:** `crates/genie-core/src/memory/inject.rs`, `crates/genie-core/src/agent_harness.rs`.",
